🏢 1. Business Problem

The company is generating strong sales, but profit is inconsistent and often negative.

👉 Objective:

Identify reasons behind losses
Analyze impact of discount, category, region, and customers
Provide actionable recommendations to improve profitability
🔍 2. Key Findings
💰 1. Sales vs Profit
High sales do not always lead to high profit
Many high-sales orders result in negative profit

👉 Insight:

Increasing sales alone is not enough; profitability depends on pricing and discount strategy

🏷️ 2. Discount Impact
Strong negative relationship between discount and profit
Higher discounts → lower profit → more losses

👉 Insight:

Excessive discounting is a major reason for loss-making orders

🛍️ 3. Category Analysis
Furniture → High sales but low profit ❌
Office Supplies → Lower sales but better profit ✅
Technology → High sales and high profit ✅

👉 Insight:

Furniture is inefficient, while Technology is the most profitable category

📦 4. Sub-Category Analysis (Root Cause)
Tables & Bookcases → Major loss contributors ❌
Chairs & Furnishings → Profitable ✅

👉 Insight:

Losses in Furniture are driven mainly by specific sub-categories

🌍 5. Region Analysis
Central region → Highest number of loss orders ❌
South region → Lowest loss orders ✅

👉 Insight:

Regional performance varies significantly; Central region needs attention

👤 6. Customer Analysis
Some customers generate consistent losses
High-frequency customers are not always profitable

👉 Insight:

Customer-level discounting and behavior impact profitability

🧠 3. Overall Conclusion

The primary reason for inconsistent profitability is aggressive discounting, especially in the Furniture category and Central region, leading to a high number of loss-making transactions.

💡 4. Business Recommendations
🏷️ 1. Optimize Discount Strategy
Limit high discounts on low-margin products
Set discount thresholds
🛍️ 2. Improve Furniture Category
Review pricing of Tables & Bookcases
Reduce discounts on these sub-categories
🌍 3. Focus on Central Region
Analyze regional pricing strategy
Control excessive discounting
👤 4. Customer Segmentation
Identify loss-making customers
Avoid giving heavy discounts to them
Reward high-profit customers
📈 5. Focus on High-Profit Areas
Invest more in Technology category
Expand in profitable regions
🚀 5. Final Outcome

If implemented, these changes can:

Reduce loss-making orders
Improve overall profit margin
Create a more sustainable business model